    <question>
        <prompt>How did the Supreme Court case Buck v. Bell impact American society?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It protected civil rights</option>
            <option letter="b">It allowed forced sterilization</option>
            <option letter="c">It expanded voting rights</option>
            <option letter="d">It regulated business practices</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Buck v. Bell (1927) allowed states to forcibly sterilize people deemed "unfit," supporting eugenics policies that disproportionately affected poor and minority populations.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was the primary impact of William Randolph Hearst on American society?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">He invented the telephone</option>
            <option letter="b">He pioneered yellow journalism</option>
            <option letter="c">He was a military leader</option>
            <option letter="d">He wrote the Constitution</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>William Randolph Hearst pioneered yellow journalism through his newspaper empire, significantly influencing public opinion and contributing to support for the Spanish-American War.</explanation>
    </question>

